<TITLE> 2000 extra police deployed at Gazipur garment factories </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, July 5 (bdnews24.com)Around two thousand additional law enforcers were deployed at Gazipur industrial zone Sunday to ensure the security of garment factories located in the area, police said. "The government and local administrators were concerned about the recent incidents of violence and vandalism in different garment factories," Gazipur police superintendent SM Mahfuzul Haque Nuruzzaman told bdnews24.com. "We suspect there may be a group plotting to destroy one of the major export orientated areas of the country," he said. "Any such attempt will be dealt with very severely," he said. Three days of riots the previous week by garment workers protesting work conditions, which left two workers dead and a factory ablaze, has been described by the industries minister among others as an attempt to "destabilise the government". bdn
